Now I have a clear picture. Here's the fix:

## Issue Summary

The Settings UI saves `IDENTITY.md` and `SOUL.md` to root (`~/.moltis/`) but the loader reads from `agents/main/` first. If agent-level files exist, UI changes are silently ignored.

## Fix (3 changes in `crates/onboarding/src/service.rs`)

### 1. Line 110 — onboarding wizard completion
```rust
// Before:
moltis_config::save_identity(&ws.identity).context("failed to save IDENTITY.md")?;

// After:
moltis_config::save_identity_for_agent("main", &ws.identity).context("failed to save IDENTITY.md")?;
```

### 2. Line 271 — `identity_update` (Settings UI)
```rust
// Before:
moltis_config::save_identity(&identity).context("failed to save identity")?;

// After:
moltis_config::save_identity_for_agent("main", &identity).context("failed to save identity")?;
```

### 3. Line 297 — `identity_update_soul` (Settings UI)

`save_soul_for_agent` doesn't exist yet, so it needs to be added to `crates/config/src/loader.rs`, mirroring the existing `save_identity_for_agent` pattern:

```rust
pub fn save_soul_for_agent(agent_id: &str, soul: Option<&str>) -> crate::Result<PathBuf> {
    let dir = agent_workspace_dir(agent_id);
    std::fs::create_dir_all(&dir)?;
    let path = dir.join("SOUL.md");
    match soul.map(str::trim) {
        Some(content) if !content.is_empty() => {
            std::fs::write(&path, content)?;
        }
        _ => {
            std::fs::write(&path, "")?;
        }
    }
    Ok(path)
}
```

Then in `service.rs:297`:
```rust
// Before:
moltis_config::save_soul(soul.as_deref()).context("failed to save soul")?;

// After:
moltis_config::save_soul_for_agent("main", soul.as_deref()).context("failed to save soul")?;
```

And export `save_soul_for_agent` from `crates/config/src/lib.rs` alongside the existing `save_identity_for_agent`.

### Why keep root `save_identity`/`save_soul`?

They serve as legacy fallback writers. The loaders already fall back to root when `agents/main/` files don't exist, so older installations without the `agents/main/` directory continue to work. No changes needed to the load paths.

Want me to implement this?

